===Etymology===
From French.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# [[exemplary|Exemplary]] of, [[decorate]]d by, or [[evocative]] of cloisonne work.
#:''Zoë wore a pair of '''cloisonne''' earrings she had bought in France.''

===Noun===
{{en-noun|cloisonne}}

# {{cattag|metalwork|uncountable}} A [[decorative]] technique for metalwork, especially [[brass]], whereby colored [[enamel]] is [[bake]]d between raised [[ridge]]s of the metal.
#:'''''Cloisonne''' is sometimes seen as a cheaper alternative to jewelled encrustation or filigree.''
# {{cattag|metalwork}} An example of such decorative [[art]], or an object decorated by it.
#:''The museum had a fine collection of medieval Italian '''cloisonne'''.